cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning and probabilistic schemes to mimic the behaviour of idiotypic robot controllers. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of control techniques (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG) in the experiments. Additionally, the probabilistic schemes used in the paper involve the use of probabilities and ranking, which are concepts commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
